.SH STANDARDS
POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008.
.SH NOTES
.BR sigwait ()
is implemented using
.BR sigtimedwait (2).
.PP
The glibc implementation of
.BR sigwait ()
silently ignores attempts to wait for the two real-time signals that
are used internally by the NPTL threading implementation.
See
.BR nptl (7)
for details.
